# Abuse of AI in Industry — Video Case Study Summary

This project is an in-depth case study presented through a Synthesia-generated video. It explores how AI can be misused in real-world industries and the consequences of unethical deployment.

## Objective
To analyze a real example of harmful AI usage, explain how the abuse occurred, and propose solutions for preventing similar incidents.

## What I Covered
- Explained the chosen industry scenario (e.g., deepfakes, surveillance misuse, biased algorithms, or automated manipulation).
- Broke down how the AI system worked and how it was exploited.
- Highlighted the ethical, social, and economic impacts of the misuse.
- Discussed accountability issues and who was affected.
- Proposed responsible AI practices and safeguards to prevent future harm.

## Key Learnings
- Understanding the risks of AI when deployed without oversight.
- Recognizing how bias, lack of transparency, or poor governance can lead to real damage.
- Importance of ethical frameworks, regulation, and human oversight.
- How video-based communication can simplify complex AI topics.

## Outcome
A clear, accessible video case study explaining the dangers of AI misuse and offering practical recommendations for safer, more responsible AI deployment.
